nal reaction stand out.\n\nAnother iPhone appears vertically in a hand with an incoming FaceTime screen. The display shows a woman’s face and readable text indicating that “Alan” would like to FaceTime, with red “Decline” and green “Accept” buttons at the bottom. A finger moves toward the green accept button. The call connects: first the man’s face appears on the phone, then the woman’s face fills the main screen with a small inset of the man in the corner. The on-screen controls include an “End” button along the bottom.\n\nThe woman on the phone appears to be a young adult with long dark hair, wearing a light blue shirt over a white top. She smiles warmly and raises a hand in greeting. The man is now seen in a bedroom, wearing a dark T-shirt, holding the iPhone in one hand while sitting near a bed with pillows behind him. He smiles at the screen and waves back. He then touches his fingers near his mouth and chin while watching her, as if communicating with gestures. She continues speaking or responding on the phone screen, her face framed clearly in the display.\n\nThe man’s expression softens into a small smile. He raises one hand toward the phone and forms a gesture with thumb, index finger, and little finger extended while the middle and ring fingers are folded down, holding it steady for her to see. On the iPhone screen, the woman lifts her hand to her mouth and blows a kiss toward him, then smiles. His finger moves near the edge of the phone as if interacting with the call controls. The woman is then visible in her own bedroom, seated on a bed and holding her iPhone upright, smiling as she taps the screen. The man looks down at his phone with a quiet, pleased smile. The image gradually fades back to white.",
